info.description:
expel.lib
=========

This is ``expel.lib`` part of the ExPeL library. It provides code to create
a networked xPL device.

Dependencies
------------

``expel.lib`` is dependent on the following Python packages...

*  `Twisted <http://twistedmatrix.com/trac/>`_
*  `ConfigObj <http://pypi.python.org/pypi/configobj>`_
*  expel.message

 
Version History
---------------

========  ====================================================================
Version	  Notes
========  ====================================================================
0.2       Module `xpllooper` renamed to `looper`
0.1       Initial release
========  ====================================================================


Source Code
-----------

The source code can be found within Launchpad at the following location
https://launchpad.net/expel

To Do
-----

* Refactor into xPLApplication, xPLLooper and xPLHandler
* Fragmented message handling
* Graphical Reactors (wx, gtk, qt etc.)

So obviously those things don't currently work.
